132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 40
H.P. 4 House of Representatives, January 8, 2025
An Act to Amend the Laws Governing the Commercial Large
Game Shooting Area License Transfer Process
Submitted by the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint
Rule 204.
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed
pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PLUECKER of Warren.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 7 MRSA §1342, sub-§5, as enacted by PL 1999, c. 765, §3, is repealed.
3 Sec. 2. 7 MRSA §1342, sub-§5-A is enacted to read:
4 5-A. Transfer of license. A person may not transfer a commercial large game
5 shooting area license without obtaining approval of the commissioner for the transfer.
6 Department approval must be obtained prior to the transfer of the license. The department,
7 at its discretion, may require that the proposed new licensee apply for a new license or may
8 approve the transfer of the existing license upon a satisfactory showing that the proposed
9 new licensee can abide by the license terms and conditions and comply with subsection 2.
10 Sec. 3. 7 MRSA §1342-A, sub-§3, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 249, §6, is amended
11 by amending the first blocked paragraph to read:
12 A license issued under this section is for a specific parcel of land and only for the genus
13 and species of large game specified in the license. The requirements and restrictions under
14 section 1342, subsections 3, 4, 5 5-A, 6 and 7 and rules adopted under subsection 8 apply
15 to licenses issued under this section. A person issued a license under this section shall
16 establish and maintain the licensed commercial large game shooting area in accordance
17 with section 1342, subsection 2, paragraphs A to E.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This bill provides the Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry with
2200 the final authority on approving a transfer of a commercial large game shooting area
2211 license. The bill provides that the proposed new licensee must meet the requirements for
2222 licensure as outlined in the statute.
